{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, effective heat redistribution occurs in the low-pressure regions, preventing much stellar heat from being transferred into the lower regions of the planet, resulting in an isothermal profile.",
    "Due to wind movement from west to east, the eastern terminator (90 • longitude, latitude ranging from 0 • -90 •) is hotter than the western terminator (270 • longitude, latitude ranging from 0 • -90 •).",
    "THOR is an altitude-based GCM model that does not converge at pressures lower than 10 -4 bar (Deitrick et al. 2022).",
    "This limitation excludes an important atmospheric region where photochemical processes are highly active.",
    "To incorporate this region, we recalculated the 1D T-P and K 𝑍 𝑍 profiles with a top-of-atmosphere pressure of 10 -8 bar and extended the temperature and K 𝑍 𝑍 profiles of all 3D models down to 10 -8 bar using isothermal extrapolation, ensuring consistency with the 1D profiles."
  ]
}